2. DAPR CONFIGURATION
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  DaprProperties:      @ConfigurationProperties(prefix = "flowforge.dapr"):
                       sidecarHost, sidecarHttpPort, sidecarGrpcPort, pubsubName,
                       stateStoreName, secretStoreName, timeout; defaults:
                       localhost:3500/50001, pubsub=flowforge-pubsub, state=flowforge-state,
                       secrets=flowforge-secrets, timeout=30s.
  DaprClientConfig:    @Configuration + @EnableConfigurationProperties(DaprProperties);
                       sets dapr.sidecar.ip, dapr.http.port, dapr.grpc.port system properties
                       and creates DaprClient via DaprClientBuilder.

3. SERVICE INVOCATION, PUB/SUB, STATE, SECRETS
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  DaprServiceInvoker:  @Service wrapper over DaprClient.invokeMethod:
                       - invoke(appId, method, request, responseType) uses HttpExtension.POST,
                         blocks with 30s timeout, records flowforge.dapr.invoke.latency by appId/method,
                         increments success/error counters and throws DaprInvocationException on failure.
                       - invokeAsync(appId, method, request) fire-and-forget with log callbacks.
  DaprEventPublisher:  @Service; publish(topic, PipelineEvent) uses DaprClient.publishEvent with
                       pubsubName from DaprProperties, metadata (content-type, cloudevent.type, source),
                       blocks with timeout; increments flowforge.dapr.pubsub.published / .error.
  DaprEventSubscriber: @RestController; exposes:
                       - GET /dapr/subscribe → DaprSubscription list for topics
                         pipeline.stage.completed, pipeline.stage.failed, pipeline.snapshot.ready.
                       - POST /api/events/stage-completed|stage-failed|snapshot-ready endpoints that
                         accept CloudEvent<PipelineEvent.*> and dispatch to PipelineEventHandler beans.
  PipelineEvent:       sealed interface with StageCompletedEvent(snapshotId,stage,duration,metadata),
                       StageFailedEvent(snapshotId,stage,error,attempt), SnapshotReadyEvent(snapshotId,repoUrls,createdAt).
  DaprStateService:    @Service; thin wrapper over DaprClient state APIs:
                       saveState(key,value[,etag]), getState(key,type)→Optional, deleteState, saveBulkState(map).
  DaprSecretService:   @Service; wraps DaprClient.getSecret/getBulkSecret to return single/multiple secrets.
  PipelineEventHandler: interface with default no-op hooks for the three event types (extension point for consumers).

4. SPRING BOOT DAPR SECRET INTEGRATION
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  DaprSecretPostProcessor: EnvironmentPostProcessor registered via
  META-INF/spring/org.springframework.boot.env.EnvironmentPostProcessor.imports.
  - Activated only when profile "dapr" is present.
  - Uses a temporary DaprClient to fetch selected secrets from secret store
    (flowforge.dapr.secret-store-name, default flowforge-secrets).
  - Maps secrets postgres-password, minio-secret-key, neo4j-password into Spring properties
    spring.datasource.password, flowforge.minio.secret-key, flowforge.neo4j.password,
    via a high-priority "daprSecrets" property source, with graceful fallback when secrets
    are unavailable.

5. K8S DAPR COMPONENTS & ARGOCD APP
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  k8s/dapr/pubsub.yaml:      Component flowforge-pubsub (pubsub.redis) pointing to Redis in flowforge-infra.
  k8s/dapr/statestore.yaml:  Component flowforge-state (state.redis) with actorStateStore=true.
  k8s/dapr/secretstore.yaml: Component flowforge-secrets (secretstores.azure.keyvault) for Key Vault flowforge-kv.
  k8s/argocd/apps/dapr.yaml: ArgoCD Application using dapr Helm chart + k8s/infrastructure/dapr/values.yaml,
                             deploys Dapr control plane into dapr-system.
  k8s/infrastructure/dapr/values.yaml: Helm values for Dapr controller/sidecar resources and telemetry.

